						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The problem with the NES version is the game is massively unbalanced and the battle line-up is a mess. The more I dug into the game, the more broken the mechanics were on the inside. Everything from level growth curves to battle maths to enemy layout is just broken. I mean, it kind of *looks* like FF7, but at it's heart the engine is just all wrong.</div><br />Of course it is just al wrong !! This "game" was "ported" by crappy Chinese pirates !! You didn't expect it to be any good, did you ?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">There is a design philosophy that all Final Fantasy games follow, starting with the first. The FF7 NES version follows it to a point, kind of, and then completely drops it. It wasn't because of space constraints, just a simple lack of knowledge of how the actual game does things. I want to correct that...</div><br />You are free to do whathever you want in your life, but to me, even though I'm a FF fan, it sounds a painful waste of time. Not that it wouldn't be interesting, I agree, but in the end this "port" of the game is a total piece of crap so you'd rather want to rewrite the whole game, and even if you did, it would be an illegal thing because FF7 belongs to Square.<br />A big part of FF7's awesomeness is in it's pre-rendered backgrounds and awesome movies. Now I agree graphics doesn't do a good game but they contribute to the overall feeling of the game's universe. This will not be possible to reproduce on the NES.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I'm going to try and squeeze a 2mb game into 512k. That might be difficult, however. I would like as much space as I can get because I can run a real risk of running out. (FYI, the actual PSX FF7 engine is 4MB, but that also includes some game data embedded in it.)</div><br />The playstation has 2MB system RAM.... I doubt the kernel is 4MB.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">* The save ram can get a little heavy. An actual FF7 PSX save is a touch over 4k. However there is a lot of irrelevant info in there when moving to NES-Space and can be cut in half.</div>
<br />A touch over 4k ? Since a playstation memory card save is 8k, exactly like the standard size of a NES battery save, I guess half of it is unused on FF7 saves then ?</div>

					
