						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">halkun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">* I can't use char-ram because I will be compressing the graphics to make things fit . I'll take the speed hit.</div><br />Do you mean you can't use CHR ROM?<br /><br />Anyway, I have some CHR compression code that you can use. It basically does pixel-level run-length encoding, and it can decode four tiles in one frame, allowing animations to be streamed into CHR RAM.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">* In a perfect world, I need a "kernel" sitting at the $C000-$FFFF that runs the whole show.</div><br />SUROM has two kernels, one for each half of the PRG ROM. If the second half of the ROM is just tile data, the second kernel can be the decompressor and not much else.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">What is an effective muti-bank template for ca65?</div>
<br />I can provide an SNROM template, and then once you finish making the Midgar episode, I can help you upgrade it to SUROM.</div>

