						<div class="postbody">Some authors <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanworkBan" class="postlink">vocally oppose</a> fan fiction, fan art, etc. But at least in my country, Square Enix won't have as much of a case if you change "Shinra" to "Square" and rewrite the dialogue to be <em>about</em> Square Enix's fanwork ban. <a href="http://www.maaco.com/" class="postlink">Maaco</a> energy is drawn from the lifestream of video game fans. Then it arguably falls under the fair use exception for comment on a copyrighted work.
<br />
<br />3gengames: At what point does it cease to be someone else's game and become one's own? Some companies are known to claim arguably uncopyrightable elements as their own exclusive property.
<br />
<br />
<br />ObTopic: <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7991" class="postlink">My recent sprite demo</a> is building in my SNROM framework. I just need to get interbank procedure calls working.</div>

