			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wikipedia says <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.bss" class="postlink">BSS</a> stands for "Block Started by Symbol". It refers to memory areas that are cleared before main() starts, as opposed to DATA segments in RAM that get something copied into them first, or RODATA segments that are placed in ROM (or in parts of RAM write-protected by the MMU).
<br />
<br />If you go with a mapper that has 32 KiB bankswitching, it looks like you're going to need a template for <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/BNROM" class="postlink">BNROM</a> (#34) and <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/AxROM" class="postlink">AOROM</a> (#7) too. Did you manage to check out the SGROM/SNROM template that I posted in the other topic?
<br />
<br />Which mapper 163 document do you think is accurate?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

