					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">halkun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">After lots of hand-wringing, swearing, and watching Captain America, I decided that the mapper to go with was the one I started with....<br /><br />Mapper 163.</div><br />I think you're getting ahead of yourself. It's not hard to change mappers once you've reached the limitations. So I'd still suggest starting with something more better known like FME-7. It supports up to 512KB of PRG (with 8KB banking), PRG-RAM (aka WRAM aka SRAM) and a nice CPU cycle based IRQ counter. FCEUX even supports 2MB PRG-ROM according to <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Sunsoft_FME-7#Emulator_Compatibility_and_Behavior">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Suns ... d_Behavior</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The issue is I would like to "assign" banks to source files.</div>
<br />You need to create a memory specification and a segment specification for each bank. In the source file then switch to the segment with ".segment".</div>

